" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 541px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Types of splicing mutations and correction with antisense morpholino oligonucleotides",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 521px; height: 667px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    A) Type I refers to the classical splicing mutation that causes the deletion of an entire exon during pre-mRNA splicing. B) Type II splicing mutations occur in the mid-intron and result in the insertion of a pseudoexon at the cDNA level. C) Type III mutations lie within the coding region, resulting in the partial deletion of an exon. D) Type IV mutations lie within the intron and lead to partial deletion of an exon. E) Type V mutations disturb the lariat branch point and result in deletion of an exon.",
